{
  "_README_PLEASE_READ": [
    "This is an ILLUSTRATIVE example, not a runnable config. Path resolution rule:",
    "  - Relative paths are resolved against config_path.resolve().parents[2].",
    "  - i.e., if you place this file at <repo>/tools/material_fit/output/<case>/fit_config.json,",
    "    parents[2] = <repo>/, and 'assets/...' below means '<repo>/assets/...'.",
    "  - When the UI persists a project, derive_fit_config writes ABSOLUTE paths to avoid this trap.",
    "  - When you write a config by hand, the safest practice is to use absolute paths everywhere.",
    "The 'assets/resources/...' paths below are taken from one specific user's Laya project layout",
    "and will NOT exist in your environment. Replace them with paths to YOUR Laya/Unity assets.",
    "cma_es.restart_center_mode accepts 'best', 'random', or 'alternate'.",
    "cma_es.restart_population_schedule accepts 'ipop' or 'bipop'.",
    "All keys starting with '_' are ignored by fit_material.py."
  ],
